systemctl enable ensures the service starts automatically when the system boots.

systemd manages background services in Linux.

Topic 2: Shell Scripting – If/Else Conditions
What I Practiced

Created a script to check whether a number is positive, negative, or zero.

Script Example
#!/bin/bash

echo "Enter a number:"
read num

if [ $num -gt 0 ]
then
  echo "Positive number"
elif [ $num -lt 0 ]
then
  echo "Negative number"
else
  echo "Number is zero"
fi
What I Re-learned

if, elif, and else are used for decision-making in shell scripts.

-gt means greater than and -lt means less than.

read is used to take input from the user.

