1️⃣ What does chmod 755 script.sh do?

chmod 755 script.sh changes the file permissions.

Owner → read, write, execute (7)

Group → read, execute (5)

Others → read, execute (5)

Example:

chmod 755 script.sh

Meaning:

Owner can read, write, execute

Others can read and execute only

Commonly used for scripts or executable files.

2️⃣ Difference between a Process and a Service
Process	Service
A running instance of a program	A background program managed by system
Temporary	Usually long-running
Example: vim, top	Example: nginx, ssh, docker

Example command to see processes:

ps aux
3️⃣ How to find which process is using port 8080?

Use:

sudo lsof -i :8080

or

sudo ss -tulnp | grep 8080

This shows the PID and program name using the port.

4️⃣ What does set -euo pipefail do in a shell script?

It makes scripts safer and fail fast.

Option	Meaning
set -e	Exit script if any command fails
set -u	Error if using undefined variable
set -o pipefail	Pipeline fails if any command fails

Example:

set -euo pipefail

Used in production scripts.

5️⃣ Difference between git reset --hard and git revert
git reset --hard	git revert
Moves HEAD and deletes changes	Creates a new commit that undoes changes
Rewrites history	Keeps history safe
Dangerous for shared branches	Safe for teams

Example:

git reset --hard HEAD~1
git revert <commit-id>
